### Watching the Safety Errors Trigger Live

Because the runtime manages the variable ledger continuously, its safety features will actively catch human errors mid-session:

```text
// Attempting to overwrite a locked Divine Constant twice
eme-gir_> {d}Nanna =ba "Moon God"
» [d] Nanna committed to memory.

eme-gir_> {d}Nanna =ba "Sun God"
--- BALA ERROR: The decree of {d}Nanna is absolute and immutable! ---

// Attempting a bad type assignment
eme-gir_> {ninda} sheep =ba "Not a number"
