## Why This Architecture Changes Things

With this REPL, we have successfully created a real execution loop. The core mechanism here—storing states inside a dynamic internal dictionary (`self.ledger`) while utilizing regular syntax scanning rules—is structurally identical to how foundational early shell environments (like basic LISP or early Python prototypes) were stood up.
